title: Musa Fires Blanks, Enyeama Can’t Stop Marseille; Onazi, Ambrose Win
text:
October 25, 2015 ↔ no comments Musa Fires Blanks, Enyeama Can’t Stop Marseille; Onazi, Ambrose Win Share Tweet + 1 Mail 
James Agberebi: 
Super Eagles skipper, Ahmed Musa, was in action for CSKA Moscow in their 0-0 draw against Terek Grozny on Sunday night. 
Musa who was on for 90 minutes, and was yellow carded in the last minute of the game. 
In the Scottish league, Eagles defender, Efe Ambrose, featured in Celtic’s 5-0 win against Dundee United. Ambrose was on throughout the game. 
Former Eagles skipper, Vincent Enyeama, was on the losing side as Lille fell 2-1 at home to Marseille in the French Ligue 1. 
And in the Italian Serie A, Eagles assistant skipper, Ogenyi Onazi, featured in Lazio’s 3-0 win against Torino. 
Onazi was later replaced by Manchester United former youth player Ravel Morrison in the 90th minute. Related
